Habit Tracker Dashboard – Google Sheets

View the live Habit Tracker dashboard here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1JrSYsC-FdZR2N8Sf2B9goOef-FE13b3ndX7-jCQnVb0/edit?usp=sharing


This project is a structured Habit Tracker Dashboard built in Google Sheets, designed to help users plan, track, and review daily habits with clarity and consistency. The tracker combines manual inputs, automated calculations, and visual indicators to provide a clear view of habit completion and progress over time.

Unlike simple checklists, this tracker is organized to reflect real-world planning workflows, focusing on usability, clean layout, and logical data flow.
 
🔧 Tools & Technologies
Google Sheets
Formulas (COUNTIF, SPARKLINE)
Checkbox automation
Progress visualization


⚙️ Key Functional Components

Daily habit tracking using checkboxes
Automatic progress calculation
Weekly progress visualization with SPARKLINE charts
Simple and clean interface
Easy to customize and add new habits


🎯 Purpose of the Project

The goal of this project is to demonstrate:
Logical sheet structuring
Practical use of Excel / Google Sheets formulas
Attention to UI clarity and user experience
Ability to build functional, real-life tracking tools, not just static spreadsheets


📂 File Information

Format: Excel / Google Sheets
Designed to scale for multiple habits and time periods


📝 Notes

Built with a neutral, professional color theme
Focused on simplicity, consistency, and usability
Suitable for productivity tracking and planning use cases
